task.summary: Default task
Added Database class to create batter, pitcher, fielder, season, and team tables. Also added methods to insert players to tables and teams to team table.
Completed changes to select 9 batters and add them to respective team lists.
Added in starting lineup to displayInfo. Added in league data for probabilities. Added averages to BatterStats.
Added in calculating visitor/home runs by inning. Added in displaying line score.
Added in reading in and selecting schedule file. New schedule file is read into team selection. Updated team runs per inning to calculate correctly. Added in logic to maintain and display line score.
Added in new method for creating and inserting lineup information from the schedules file.
Added in method for creating pgbs_schedule table as well as method for reading in a game log file and inserting it into the pgbs_schedule table.
Added in logic to insert all batting orders to pgbs_lineups. Fixed logic for fielders, batters, pitchers to pull from schedule files for the game in question.
Added in logic to select batters based on batting order.
Changed batter and fielder starters lists to HashMaps to make it easier to add and remove batters/fielders to those lists and keep them at 9.
Added in logic for pitchers entering the game show in batting and fielding stats.

Fixed bug with pitchers who did not have a position assigned of 'PITCHER' and were causing a nullPointerException when they got on base and then checked for a steal. Position is now assigned to both the batter and fielder lists when the pitcher comes into the game.
Added logic for pitchOuts and added a stolenBaseAttemptPercentage and stolenBaseAttemptSuccessPercentage for calculating successful stolen bases or not.
Fixed issue with Winning/Losing Pitcher not accurately displaying when home team wins in bottom of last inning.
Added in logic for pinch hitting for the #8 hitter when 7th or greater inning and run difference < 5.

Fixed a bug where fielders were not being accurately put in fielding lineup for position from database. Checked the Retrosheet data and determined that 1913 was as far back as I could go to start a season without having to automate lineup creation.

Added in logic for updating batter, pitcher, and fielder stats to the database following completion of a game. Also added in the setting of seasonal data for batter, pitcher, and fielder when selected so they can be updated with game information.
Added in the updates to schedule file and stats. Added in the updates to teams file and stats.

Added daysRest to database build. Fixed nullPointerException due to batters bunting on base. Fixed log5 method for PitchRestult. Added check for caughtStealing for leagues that didn't record it. Adjusted stolen bases for additional criteria to check. Added calculating complete games and shutouts for pitchers.
Parallax index.html and style.css code.
Added in configuration and coding for Spring Boot.
Made lots of changes. Trying to save this and start another branch but don't want to lose this code. Will merge in later.
Added more stuff that was not added before.
Getting things back to working in master. Added in css styles and images. Will build from this.

Application, controllers, and repositories work. Will retrieve list of relievers from reliever table in db as well as retrieve a single reliever with the /find?playerId= URI. Currently does not display any of the other pages however.
Removed the Hibernate stuff. Just going to use straight SQL for database access through jdbc. Set up DAO and Impls for reliever class. This now works correctly.
Added Thymeleaf functionality to create tables and also to have links within those tables.
Now fully functioning website. All links work.
Added loading of simulated standings to home page.
Contains the grid layout that I like. Need to convert over to index.html file though.
Home page team standings works. Leaders layout looks good but needs to have the actual data pulled and input.
Changed to use MaterialDesign for Bootstrap.

- created table for standings in js - changed the header - added Standings instead of Seasons and changed order - created Standings page and moved from Front Office to the standings page - scaled down the Front Office page - created Coming Soon landing page for all Schedule, Leaders, and Teams - added selectors for Stats page

- fixed option value for select dropdown on Standings page - added in populating the standings on change of year select - added sortable table to Stats page for hitting - added styling for active buttons on Stats page - moved check users to server side - sign-in page clears out input value when invalid username is entered - added coords for logos for 1913 teams - added ability to select league (MLB, AL, or NL) for stats page
- adding table for Schedule page

- added query to pull schedule data from the database - fixed date on schedule page to display month and day - fixed display on schedule page to display one month at a time - added button for BOX or PLAY to schedule page depending on whether game was completed or not
- Added in html and css for the box score page

- got Session to work and to be able to display session information on the Front Office page - fielding stats are being added into the boxscore but I do not believe they are being properly calculated/applied - pitcher stats are being added into the boxscore for a game - added ability to play a game from the schedule page (currently doesn't play the selected game but the next game available)

- added username as input parameter to getYears() in SeasonDao and SeasonDaoImpl - added simName in where clause of query in getYears() to use username to limit the query - schedulePage.html builds out the year select using Thymeleaf instead of js - schedulePage builds out the schedule results using Thymeleaf instead of js - Box on schedulePage now re-directs to box score page for the relevant gameKey - added ability to submit user by hitting Enter key - added league selectors to schedulePage.html - tied in the league selectors to schedulePage to actually limit schedule results by selected option (MLB, AL, NL) - deleted index.html file and routed HomeController to point to perfectGameHome for both "/home" and "/"

- added visiting and home scores to boxScorePage - fixed logos to load logos by year and ID for teams - added win/loss records to schedule page for pitchers following a game - fixed schedulePage so that after playing a game and closing the modal the page will reload to the current league - fixed schedulePage where it will start the right league based off the AL/NL league selector. - fixed schedulePage to play the game selected by the button

- added visiting and home team full names to boxScorePage - added logic to display batter data from model given to boxScorePage - fixed issue with incorrect stats being added to pgbs_box_score which lead to poor data being displayed in application - fixed issue with 'Game Completed' remaining in the Play modal when clicking it second time - fixed issue on boxScorePage with blue highlight not showing up on winning team score - added pitchers display to the boxScorePage

- added ability to register a user and update the database - updated players page to include information from the select for player data - schedulePage: - added DataTable which provides a better table - added pagination for months APR - OCT - changes data based on league selected as well as the month selected - wired in play functionality to schedulePage - added ability to select what type of game to display, Available/Simulated/All
